    <p>The Custom Domain is an <i>optional</i> feature that allows you to direct your customers to a custom domain like www.yourcoolpage.com instead of yourcoolpage.gumroad.com.</p>
    <h3 id="dns">DNS Configuration</h3>
    <p>First, you need to set up the DNS records with your domain registrar. If your domain is www.example.com, your DNS records should be as follows:</p>
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Host name </strong></td>
          <td><strong> Record type </strong></td>
          <td><strong> Value</strong></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td> www</td>
          <td> CNAME</td>
          <td> domains.gumroad.com</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td> @</td>
          <td> URL redirect</td>
          <td><a href="https://www.example.com">https://www.example.com</a></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>If you’d like your domain to be example.com (without www), your DNS records should be as follows:</p>
    <table><colgroup><col width="151"><col width="168"><col width="305"></colgroup>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Host name</td>
          <td>Record type</td>
          <td>Value</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>@</td>
          <td>CNAME</td>
          <td>domains.gumroad.com</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p>Note: For the CNAME record, you need to put "domains.gumroad.com," not {username}.gumroad.com. We also provide support for custom domains through CNAME records, so you don't have to re-configure nameservers for it.</p>
    <h3 id="subdomains">Subdomains</h3>
    <p>If you wish to use a subdomain, like store.example.com, your DNS records should be as follows:</p>
    <table>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><strong>Host name </strong></td>
          <td><strong> Record type </strong></td>
          <td><strong> Value</strong></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td> store</td>
          <td> CNAME</td>
          <td> domains.gumroad.com</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <h3 id="settings">Update your Gumroad settings</h3>
    <p>There are two ways to add a custom domain name on Gumroad. </p>
    <ul>
      <li><a href="#Custom-domains-for-profiles-0pt96" target="_self">Custom domains for profiles</a> allow you to set a domain for your entire profile. This means your profile and the products within it will all show up under your custom domain.</li>
      <li><a href="#Custom-domains-for-products-vk1Jr" target="_self">Custom domains for products</a> allow you to set a custom domain for just an individual product.</li>
    </ul>
    <h3 id="Custom-domains-for-profiles-0pt96">Custom domains for profiles</h3>
    <p>To set up a custom domain for your profile:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Navigate to your Gumroad <a href="https://gumroad.com/settings/advanced">Advanced settings</a></li>
      <li>Enter your domain name in the “Custom domain” section and click “Verify” on the right. </li>
      <li>If you see a failure message, recheck your DNS settings and wait for 24-48 hours for them to propagate. </li>
      <li>Click “Update settings” to save your changes.</li>
    </ol>
    <figure><%= image_tag "https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/j3hrqxTdBnIAbtRX5JiVCdZJV3TLfGjUwx4Iiwa0MyJRkYLMTfB59ijVwm22k3jB8MYgCwtvAN_FUbvhaCGo7iBn1qpG6OeG-ZU5XO93xKEAocU648-mSQtxQ9kSXFF0Ir52INy0YWzybBVr31SBqag" %></figure>
    <h3 id="Custom-domains-for-products-vk1Jr">Custom domains for products</h3>
    <p>To set up a custom domain for an individual product:</p>
    <ol>
      <li>Navigate to the “edit” page of that product. </li>
      <li>Enter your domain name in the “Custom domain” section and click “Verify” on the right.</li>
      <li>If you see a failure message, recheck your DNS settings and wait for 24-48 hours for them to propagate. </li>
      <li>Click “Save changes” to save your changes.</li>
    </ol>
